identifications.body:
Lovely photo!!!!
My vote is for  Lilium pardalinum because it the name attached to the wild ones here. Lilium lancifolium (syn. L. tigrinum) is an Asian species of lily, native to China, Japan, Korea, and the Russian Far East. It is widely planted as an ornamental. But I bet, given a chance, they would interbreed, which makes them the same species in my view, if the offspring are fertile.
